-- Threadneedle Hires Legal & General's Burgess as Chief Investment Officer
-- Kevin Crowley
-- 2010-07-13T09:46:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-13/threadneedle-hires-legal-general-s-burgess-as-chief-investment-officer.html

          
          
             Threadneedle Asset Management Ltd. ,
the London-based asset-management unit of Ameriprise Financial
Inc., appointed  Legal & General Group Plc ’s  Mark Burgess  as its
chief investment officer.  
 Burgess, 45, will start the role in the first quarter of
2011 and will succeed  Sarah Arkle , Threadneedle said today in an
e-mailed statement. Burgess’s previous post was head of equities
at Legal & General Investment Management, the biggest investor
in the U.K. stock market.  
 Burgess, who joined Legal & General in 2003, is the second
senior departure from Legal & General Investment Management this
year. Chief Executive Officer  Peter Chambers  said in March he
plans to retire by September and a successor hasn’t yet been
announced.  
 “The appointment of such a high-caliber industry figure as
Mark Burgess means that we are well positioned to build on
Sarah’s impressive legacy,” Threadneedle Chairman  Simon Davies 
said in the statement.  
 Arkle, who has been CIO for 10 years, will retire in 2011
and become a vice chairman at Threadneedle, the company said.  
